<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="926" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[112,648,216,465]" box="[113,213,216,242]" pageId="9" pageNumber="926">REMARKS</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[112,648,216,465]" pageId="9" pageNumber="926">
The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Blanchard" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[442,571,247,273]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Heptomera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="926" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metallica">
<emphasis box="[442,571,247,273]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="926">E. metallica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the smaller body size, the lacking posterior elytral declivity, the longitudinally impressed elytral punctures, the unfused antennomeres 3-5, and the shape of male genitalia having the parameres more elongate and weakly curved interiorly, without an apical hook.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
